race.comment: LES BRAVES (3) should take some beating, especially post-scratchings with a handful of dangers coming out. His form this time in reads well, winning comfortably fresh before two close-up efforts in what look like stronger races. He has been beaten as favourite in both but has run well, and while drawn wide, if he has a back to follow he can prove too strong late. THE OPPORTUNIST (8) has been okay in two runs back and should be better for them. Can forgive the last one on tough ground. TWO WOLVES (2) resumes. He won on debut here over 1400m and wasn't far away in town before a spell. Respecting fresh. THE VOLTA (10) is lightly raced and should be better suited to 1200m off an even return at Mornington.
